    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Entoprocta is treated as a class of phylum Kamotozoa, rather than as a full phylum. Group of small, aquatic invertebrate animals composed of about 150 species and subdivided into four families. Entoprocts occur throughout the world, primarily in marine habitats, although one genus is a freshwater form. </Note_Text>
